      "body": "v4.31 recipes round 3 (MR0555258 migration): convert descends deeper, Type-hom funext wall, structInst binder-field parse quirk\n\nNew patterns from migrating `MR0555258/Basic.lean` v4.30\u2192v4.31 (all verified green, complement the existing v4.31 memories):\n\n- **`convert h using N` descends one level deeper in v4.31**: proofs shaped `convert h using 4; exact congrArg f e` break with a type-mismatch whose 'expected' is the *argument-level* equality. Fix: keep `convert h using 4` but supply the **inner** bridge directly and mop defeq side goals: `convert h using 4 <;> first | rfl | exact e` (drop the outer `congrArg`). Extra side goals are object/category equalities closed by `rfl`.\n- **Type-category hom equality: `funext`/`apply funext` does NOT unify** with `f \u226b g = h \u226b i` even under `respectTransparency false`. Mathlib's own idiom (see `FullyFaithful.homNatIso`): `fun f => by ext g; exact hF.map_injective (by simp)`. If simp stalls on `hG.homEquiv.symm` (v4.31 displays via `ConcreteCategory.hom ... .toFun`), run `simp` first, then `show`-restate with `hG.preimage` (defeq to `homEquiv.symm`), then `simp` (fires `map_preimage`).\n- **StructInst binder-style field + comma**: `{ app V := e, naturality := ... }` fails to parse ('unexpected identifier; expected }'). Use lambda + newline-separated fields: `{ app := fun V => e\\n  naturality := ... }`.\n- **`Scheme.Hom.appIso_inv_naturality` exists in v4.31 Mathlib** \u2014 exact match for presheaf-map-vs-appIso.inv naturality squares of open immersions; no hand proof needed.\n- **`lake update` with a dep pinned to `main` (doc-gen4) silently bumps `lean-toolchain`** (to v4.32.0-rc1 here) and then the mathlib cache refuses to fetch. Pin doc-gen4 to `0bc516c1b9db` (the AJC rev) and rewrite `lean-toolchain` back before re-running.\n- MR0555258 iterates at ~110 s per `lake build` of `Basic.lean`; mathlib cache is shared locally (no download needed).",
